excerpt: Historic 18th-century lighthouse featuring tower climbs with ocean vistas, a gift shop & more.
detail_description: Nestled at the entrance of Chesapeake Bay, the Cape Henry Lighthouse is a historic gem that dates back to 1791. This iconic structure was pivotal in ensuring safe navigation for vessels entering the harbor, marking a significant milestone in maritime history. Constructed from Aquia sandstone—similar to that used in many Washington, DC buildings—the lighthouse stands as a testament to early American engineering and federal investment. Visitors can climb its tower for breathtaking ocean views and explore its charming gift shop filled with unique souvenirs.
name: Cape Henry Lighthouse
address: 583 Atlantic Ave, Fort Story, VA 23459, USA

excerpt: Aquarium focused on Virginia marine life, past & present, with an IMAX theater, boat tour & aviary.
detail_description: The Virginia Aquarium & Marine Science Center is a captivating destination that immerses visitors in the wonders of marine life native to Virginia, both past and present. Nestled just a mile from downtown, this attraction boasts over 300 interactive exhibits, including touch pools where you can get hands-on with stingrays and horseshoe crabs. The experience doesn't stop there; guests can marvel at an impressive array of creatures such as turtles, sharks, otters, and even Komodo dragons.
name: Virginia Aquarium & Marine Science Center
address: 717 General Booth Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Cape Henry beachfront park & historic site with marshes, maritime forest, hiking & canoe trails.
detail_description: First Landing State Park, situated on the Cape Henry beachfront, is a historic site and natural haven boasting marshes, maritime forests, hiking trails, and canoe routes. This park is a popular destination in the Hampton Roads metro area due to its coastal location and numerous outdoor activities. It's also recognized as Virginia's first planned park and holds a place on the Register of Historic Places as Seashore State Park Historic District.
name: First Landing State Park
address: 2500 Shore Dr, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Former landfill now a city recreational area with a skate park, picnicking & sports facilities.
detail_description: Mount Trashmore Park, located in Virginia Beach, is a unique recreational area that was once a landfill but has been transformed into a vibrant community hub. Covering 165 acres, the park features two man-made mountains, two lakes, playgrounds, and a skatepark with a vert ramp. The main mountain, Mount Trashmore, stands at 60 feet tall and offers opportunities for hiking and picnicking. This eco-friendly space also includes multi-use pathways for walking and cycling.
name: Mount Trashmore Park
address: 310 Edwin Dr, Virginia Beach, VA 23462, USA

excerpt: Pristine maritime forest & coastline not accessible by private car, with biking trails & kayaking.
detail_description: False Cape State Park, located between Back Bay and the Atlantic Ocean, offers a back-to-nature experience with its pristine maritime forest and coastline. Accessible only by hiking or boating in, the park features 15 miles of trails, untouched beaches for sunbathing and swimming, guided kayak trips, and beachfront primitive camping. Visitors can explore the historic Wash Woods community and enjoy outdoor activities such as hiking, biking through various trails, kayaking trips, beachcombing, and camping.
name: False Cape State Park
address: 4001 Sandpiper Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Vintage WWI & WWII military planes, many still in flying shape, are housed in this hangar museum.
detail_description: Nestled in the scenic Sandbridge area of Virginia Beach, the Military Aviation Museum is a treasure trove for aviation enthusiasts and history buffs alike. This impressive museum boasts one of the largest private collections of vintage military aircraft from World War I and II, many of which are still capable of flight. Visitors can explore over 100 acres filled with meticulously restored planes that played significant roles in military history, including iconic fighters and bombers.
name: Military Aviation Museum
address: 1341 Princess Anne Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23457, USA

excerpt: Wetlands refuge that hosts thousands of migratory waterfowl, including snow geese & tundra swans.
detail_description: Back Bay National Wildlife Refuge is a haven for migratory waterfowl, such as snow geese and tundra swans. The refuge spans several miles of beach and marshlands, providing protection from development. Visitors can explore the area through various trails that wind through untouched coastal habitat. In addition to birdwatching, outdoor enthusiasts can enjoy hiking, biking, or leisurely strolls in the warmer months.
name: Back Bay National Wildlife Refuge
address: 4005 Sandpiper Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Regularly changing exhibitions of art such as paintings, sculptures & photography, plus classes.
detail_description: Immerse yourself in the vibrant art scene of Virginia Beach by visiting the Virginia Museum of Contemporary Art (MOCA). This museum offers a dynamic experience with its ever-changing exhibitions featuring paintings, sculptures, and photography. You can also participate in studio art classes and attend special events to deepen your understanding of contemporary art. As you explore the ViBe Creative District, take a leisurely stroll on the Mural Walking Tour to admire outdoor murals created by local artists.
name: Virginia Museum of Contemporary Art
address: 2200 Parks Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Water slides, a tubing river & a wave pool headline this sprawling water park with 30+ rides.
detail_description: Ocean Breeze Waterpark is a vibrant oasis located just two miles south of the Oceanfront in Virginia Beach, making it an ideal destination for families seeking adventure and fun. Since its opening in 1974, this water park has become a beloved summer retreat, welcoming visitors from Memorial Day to Labor Day.
name: Ocean Breeze
address: 849 General Booth Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Quiet seaside enclave south of Virginia Beach featuring a sandy shoreline, vacation houses & condos.
detail_description: Sandbridge Beach is a serene coastal retreat located just 15 miles south of the bustling Virginia Beach. This 5-mile stretch of sandy shoreline offers a peaceful alternative to the more touristy areas, making it perfect for swimmers, surfers, and families seeking a quieter beach experience. The proximity to vacation rentals and the nearby Back Bay National Wildlife Refuge and False Cape State Park add to its allure.
name: Sandbridge Beach
address: Virginia Beach, VA, USA

excerpt: Seasonal amusement center featuring 16 rides, a go-kart track, midway games & food stands.
detail_description: Located in Virginia Beach, the Atlantic Fun Park is a seasonal amusement center that offers a wide range of attractions for visitors of all ages. From classic rides to thrilling roller coasters and go-kart tracks, this family-friendly park provides an old-school charm with a mix of modern excitement. Situated along the boardwalk near 15th Street, it features a 100-foot Ferris wheel, midway games, food stands, and various children's and family rides.
name: Atlantic Fun Park
address: 233 15th St, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Farm with seasonal markets & family-friendly attractions including a petting zoo & bird aviary.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Virginia Beach, Hunt Club Farm is a delightful family-owned destination that spans over thirty acres of picturesque farmland. This charming farm offers an array of seasonal attractions perfect for visitors of all ages. Kids can enjoy hands-on experiences at the Petting Farm, where they can interact with friendly animals like pigs, llamas, and goats. The BirdWalk Aviary is another highlight, featuring over 500 colorful parakeets that are sure to captivate young and old alike.
name: Hunt Club Farm
address: 2388 London Bridge Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Fully accessible beach park featuring a playground, raised sand tables, a sensory board & more.
detail_description: Grommet Island Park, located in Virginia Beach, is a unique and fully accessible beach park designed to cater to individuals of all abilities. Spanning approximately 15,000 square feet, the park features a variety of inclusive amenities such as a sway boat, raised sand tables for building sandcastles at an accessible height, and a sensory board tailored for visually impaired and autistic children.
name: Grommet Island Park
address: Boardwalk &, 2nd St, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: White clapboard museum devoted to coastal rescue missions & shipwrecks plus a nautical gift shop.
detail_description: The Virginia Beach Surf & Rescue Museum is a charming white clapboard establishment that pays homage to the area's maritime heritage and the brave surf rescue teams who have safeguarded its shores. Nestled within the historic DeWitt Cottage, this museum delves into the evolution of beach safety, highlighting the vital contributions of lifeguards and shipwreck rescuers throughout history.
name: Virginia Beach Surf & Rescue Museum
address: 2401 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: April azaleas are the showstoppers at this lush green space, which also features 450 rose varieties.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Norfolk, Virginia, the Norfolk Botanical Garden spans an impressive 155 acres and is a true paradise for nature enthusiasts. This vibrant garden showcases over forty themed areas, each offering its own unique charm. In April, visitors are treated to stunning displays of azaleas that steal the spotlight alongside an extensive collection of 450 rose varieties. Among its many attractions, you'll find a serene Japanese Garden designed in traditional style with hills and ponds that invite tranquility.
name: Norfolk Botanical Garden
address: 6700 Azalea Garden Rd, Norfolk, VA 23518, USA

detail_description: Located on the Virginia Beach resort strip, Nightmare Mansion is a renowned haunted house that has been terrifying visitors for over three decades. Considered one of America's most frightening haunted houses, it offers a spine-chilling experience for thrill-seekers and ghost enthusiasts. With realistic props, sound effects, and trained actors creating ghoulish scenes, this attraction provides an adrenaline rush that is not for the faint-hearted. The narrow hallways of the mansion were once home to Dr.
name: Nightmare Mansion
address: 2008 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Veteran 17.6-mi. bridge-tunnel & "engineering wonder" crossing at the mouth of the Chesapeake Bay.
detail_description: The Chesapeake Bay Bridge-Tunnel is a remarkable 17.6-mile bridge-tunnel system that serves as an engineering marvel at the mouth of the Chesapeake Bay. It provides a seamless connection between Virginia's Eastern Shore and the mainland, offering travelers a scenic and convenient way to cross the bay. Completed in 1964, this iconic structure was designed to eliminate the reliance on ferries for transporting passengers and cargo, making it an essential part of Virginia's transportation network.
name: Chesapeake Bay Bridge-Tunnel
address: Virginia, USA

excerpt: Venerable wood fishing pier, open seasonally, with a tackle shop, seafood restaurant & rod rentals.
detail_description: The Virginia Beach Fishing Pier is a beloved seasonal wooden pier offering a tackle shop, seafood restaurant, and rod rentals. It's a family-friendly spot where you can spend an afternoon trying your luck at catching roundheads, trout, whiting, Spanish mackerel, and blue crab. Whether you're an experienced angler or just starting out, the pier welcomes all to enjoy fishing and crabbing without needing a license or equipment.
name: Virginia Beach Fishing Pier
address: 1413 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Beach park on 130+ acres with swimming, fishing & crabbing plus picnic shelters & sports courts.
detail_description: Little Island Park, located in Sandbridge near Back Bay National Wildlife Refuge, offers over 130 acres of outdoor fun. The park features a 400-foot fishing pier and a pristine beach for swimming, fishing, and beachcombing. Visitors can also enjoy picnic shelters and sports courts throughout the park. Additionally, it's a great spot for kids to play near the pier or rent fat-tire bikes from Surf and Adventure Co. to ride on the sand.
name: Little Island Park
address: 3820 Sandpiper Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

detail_description: Virginia Beach is a haven for beer enthusiasts, offering a variety of breweries to explore. Back Bay Brewing Co. and Commonwealth Brewing Company are popular choices, each with its own unique atmosphere and selection of beers. Smartmouth Pilot House, located just blocks from the Oceanfront, offers a dog-friendly outdoor drinking space in a former post office. Tarnished Truth Distilling Company stands out as the first in-hotel distillery in the United States, situated within The Historic Cavalier Hotel & Beach Club.
name: Tarnished Truth Distilling Co.
address: 4200 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA
